This paper deals with machine learning models and their impact on fairness, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). It also discusses societal and legal concerns, which could be classified under the sub-category of cyberlaw (cs.CY). The paper evaluates fairness using statistical measures, which could be classified under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning models to make decisions could also be classified under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of data preparation techniques on fairness, which could be classified under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
